    "On examination, there is a visible asymmetry of the right mandible with marked swelling extending from the right zygoma to below the lower mandibular border.",
    "Intraoral examination reveals a palpable hard mass in the right mandible, approximately 4×4 cm, palpable from the first molar to the anterior ramus border.",
    "The submandibular lymph nodes on the right are palpable, firm, and immobile.",
    "The lesion is tender for palpation.",
    "The panoramic radiograph shows a large, irregularly circumscribed, radiolucent lesion in the right mandibular body and ramus."
